  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (ML-augmented)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for a machine-learning surrogate model of CFD hemolysis prediction for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the ML surrogate can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. The surrogate was trained on CFD-derived shear-stress histories and validated against a held-out test set drawn from the same operating-condition distribution as training. Nominal-condition accuracy (R²=0.97, RMSE<0.003) is reported. Distribution-shift robustness is noted as studied separately; no linked evidence is provided.",
