      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study (coarse 1.2 M cells, medium 3.6 M cells, fine 9.1 M cells) was performed for the FDA centrifugal pump geometry. Grid-convergence index (GCI) for the volume-averaged scalar shear stress was 1.4% between medium and fine meshes. Training labels were generated on the fine mesh. Required level 2 is met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental validation test conditions span the nominal operating envelope of the CPB device (flow 2–6 L/min; speed 2000–4000 RPM).",
      "rationale": "Experimental hemolysis measurements were collected at five flow-speed combinations spanning the nominal CPB operating envelope. Inlet hematocrit (35–40%), temperature (37°C), and blood viscosity were controlled per ISO 10993-4 protocols. All test conditions fall within the nominal design space used for surrogate training. No off-nominal, degraded-fluid, or perturbed-inlet conditions were tested."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Surrogate-predicted relative hemolysis index RH agrees with experimental measurements within ±15% across all validation operating points.",
      "rationale": "Surrogate predictions of RH were compared against experimental plasma-free haemoglobin measurements converted to RH. Maximum deviation was 11.3% at the 6 L/min, 4000 RPM operating point. All five operating points satisfied the ±15% acceptance band. Comparison was performed exclusively at nominal conditions; no perturbed or shifted operating conditions were included."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
