    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels for Model Risk Level 2. Nominal-condition validation demonstrates R²=0.97 and maximum RH deviation of 11.3%, satisfying the ±15% acceptance criterion. The assessment team notes that robustness under real-world distribution shift (manufacturing tolerance variation, patient-population haematocrit shift, sensor noise) has been identified as a future workstream; however, this gap was not considered disqualifying at MRL 2 given the medium model influence and the availability of physical testing as a confirmatory check. No linked robustness evidence was reviewed as part of this package.",
